author: Inside Edition
description: Actor Chevy Chase has had a legendary show business career, from appearing in "Saturday Night Live" to starring in films like "Fletch," "Three Amigos" and the "National Lampoon's" franchise, to the sitcom "Community." "I'm Chevy Chase And You're Not," a new documentary from CNN, reveals for the first time that in 2021, Chase was hospitalized for heart failure. The comedian was in a coma for eight days, leading to memory loss.
title: Chevy Chase Almost Died In 2021

author: Inside Edition
description: There's good reason to be cautious this season, as just-released numbers from the CDC show a surge in flu cases. The outbreak is causing some people to pull the plug on big celebrations. Thankfully, there are steps you can take to avoid the flu. They include wearing a mask, washing your hands, and absolutely no kissing strangers at the stroke of midnight! If you are exposed to the flu, there are things you can do to lessen the symptoms.
title: Super Flu Outbreak Causes Travel Plan Upset

author: Inside Edition
description: Surveillance cameras captured a car crashing into a Las Vegas-area backyard. The car's driver was flung out of the vehicle, landing in a swimming pool. Homeowner Cletis Reed was about to relax in his hot tub when the accident happened. He told Inside Edition, "It sounded like a freight train." Reed waded into the pool to help, while one witness called 911. Another witness helped Reed pull the driver from the pool.
title: Driver Crashes Car And Lands In Backyard Pool

author: Inside Edition
description: Where is so-called “doomsday mom” Elleshia Anne Seymour? Seymour was last seen at an airport with four children, boarding a plane to Europe. Her husband says she became obsessed with the belief that the world is coming to an end, and that she took her kids and fled the country. The Utah mom has been charged with four counts of custodial interference. Utah's West Jordan Police Department and the FBI are working on the case. Inside Edition's Steven Fabian has more.
title: Where Is 'Doomsday Mom' Elleshia Anne Seymour?

author: Inside Edition
description: Amid the New Year’s celebrations in Times Square, a massive police operation is underway to foil any potential terror attack. The major threat is from so-called “lone wolf” terrorists. An FBI alert says "Lone offenders remain a particular concern due to their ability to avoid detection." The entire New York Police Department, which is the largest in the US, will be deployed tonight. That's 34,000 officers.
title: Law Enforcement Looking Out For New Year’s Terror Threats

author: Inside Edition
description: Outgoing U.S. Representative Marjorie Taylor Greene was once a close ally of President Trump.
title: What Marjorie Taylor Greene Said About The Women Around Trump #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A highway patrolman witnessed a terrifying scene on a bridge and it was caught on his bodycam. The Ohio State Highway Patrol says officers were responding to a vehicle that slid off the road, when the same thing happened to a semi-truck on the other side of the highway. It seemed to take a pickup truck with it. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Semi-Truck Skids Off Ohio Highway Taking Another Vehicle With It

author: Inside Edition
description: Actor Isiah Whitlock Jr. has died. He was best known for playing Senator Clay Davis in HBO's "The Wire," which ran from 2002 to 2008. His character became a fan favorite with a popular catchphrase, which seemed to follow him wherever he took an acting job. Whitlock appeared in many Spike Lee Joints, including 2002's "The 25th Hour." The director paid tribute to him on social media, referring to Whitlock as his dear, beloved brother.
title: 'The Wire' Actor Isiah Whitlock Jr. Dead At 71

author: Inside Edition
description: In October, a masked trio was caught on doorbell camera demanding entry to a home in Virginia. Thankfully, it turned out to be a Halloween prank. In May, ten fugitives were seen on surveillance cameras fleeing a New Orleans prison, sparking a massive manhunt. They have all since been recaptured. In August, dashcams caught a brightly burning meteor falling through the sky. It crashed through the roof of a Georgia home.
title: The Most Dramatic Caught On Tape Moments Of 2025

author: Inside Edition
description: Last month, Tatiana Schlossberg revealed in an essay in the New Yorker that she had terminal cancer. In her essay, Tatiana wrote that doctors told her she had maybe one more year to live. It turned out to be just weeks, as today her family shared the sad news that she had died from leukemia.
title: JFK's Granddaughter Is Dead At 35 #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: They are two of the longest unsolved crimes in American history, inspiring countless theories, books and films. The Zodiac Killer was linked to five murders in the late 1960s; the 1947 Black Dahlia case centered around the killing of Elizabeth Short, a young Hollywood hopeful. Now, a retired LAPD homicide detective has made a startling claim about these cold cases: he says the crimes were committed by the same killer.
title: Were the Zodiac and Black Dahlia Crimes Committed By The Same Killer?

author: Inside Edition
description: Pop star Taylor Swift is getting a reputation for generous gifts and gratuities to the workers around her. This year, the singer gave a $600 cash tip to a worker at Arrowhead Stadium, home of the Kansas City Chiefs, for working on Christmas Day. Swift also donated $1 million each to Feeding America and the American Heart Association. And at the conclusion of her Eras tour, Swift gave nearly $200 million in tips to the concert crew that supported her.
title: Taylor Swift Gives Huge Gifts To End The Year
